      "message": "nit: Could we replace this magic number `3` with a named constant or\nadd a brief comment? It took me a moment to figure out what these\n3 bytes correspond to.\n\nPer the NSM spec, the XID event payload is structured as:\n\n    struct nsm_xid_event_payload {\n        uint8_t  flag;            // 1 byte\n        uint8_t  reserved[3];     // \u003c- this skip(3)\n        uint32_t reason;          // 4 bytes\n        uint32_t sequence_number; // 4 bytes\n        uint64_t timestamp;       // 8 bytes\n    } __attribute__((packed));\n\nSo the `3` here is the `reserved[3]` field (alignment padding before\n`reason`). Something like the following would make this self-documenting:\n\n    constexpr size_t xidEventReservedBytes \u003d 3;\n    buffer.unpack(flags);\n    buffer.skip(xidEventReservedBytes);\n    buffer.unpack(eventMessageReason);\n\nOr alternatively, just a one-line comment:\n\n    buffer.skip(3);  // reserved[3] padding before reason (NSM XID event payload)\n\nEither works for me — whichever you prefer. Thanks!",
